    "department": "Health Practitioners",
    "description": "Alan is looking for dedicated GPs in Belgium to help transform Healthcare together! 🌟\n\n\n🐼 WHO WE ARE\n\nAlan is not just a health insurance company; we are the health partner, dedicated to the physical and mental well-being of our members every day. Since our establishment in 2016 in France, we have expanded our services to three countries (🇫🇷, 🇧🇪, 🇪🇸) and proudly support more than 500,000 members.\n\n\nOur innovative approach places equal emphasis on prevention and treatment, making healthcare more accessible and holistic.\n\n\n🇧🇪 OUR SERVICES IN BELGIUM\n\nToday we offer two services in Belgium for which we are looking for motivated family physicians:\n\n - Teleconsultations: Connect with our members via video call and offer medical advice from the comfort of your own home or practice. \n\n - Medical Chat: Engage with our members via our medical chat service, available 7 days a week, from 9 a.m. to 9 p.m. You will provide fast, accurate and personalized medical advice within a 4-hour response time. So our members get the advice, when and where they need it.\n\nGPs can apply for either service. It is not necessary to do both.\n\n\n⭐ WHY WORK FOR ALAN?\n\n - Innovative Healthcare: Be at the forefront of healthcare innovation, making healthcare more accessible and working with cutting-edge technologies.\n\n - Professional growth : discover new and innovative ways to help your patients\n\n - Online \u0026 Flexible Terms: Enjoy the flexibility to work from the comfort of your own home or practice, with a schedule that fits your needs as a primary care physician. A perfect complement to your existing practice!\n\n - Competitive Compensation: We offer competitive and market based compensation.\n\n - Team of healthcare professionals: Join our dedicated team of healthcare professionals..\n\n\n🤩 REQUIREMENTS\n\n - Certified General Practitioner: with a 003 or 004 RIZIV/INAMI number and experience in patient care.\n\n - Language Skills: Proficiency in Dutch required + either English or French\n\n - Digital Skills: Familiar with the use of digital tools.\n\n - Empathy \u0026 Communication: Excellent communication skills and strong empathetic approach to patient care.\n\n - Licensed Software: Must possess licensed prescription and attestation software.\n\n\n\n\n\nOUR RECRUITMENT PROCESS\n\n\nThe recruitment process consists of two stages. Each stage will provide an opportunity for you to ask questions as we want to ensure the best fit for both you and Alan.\n\nThe first interview will be with the Health Professional team coordinator at Alan, and will last approximately 30 minutes. The purpose is to get to know each other, clarify the project, and determine if your profile aligns with our needs.\n\nThe second interview (~45 minutes) will be with our Medical Lead (General Practitioner). The goal is to discuss a clinical case, and your clinical experiences and knowledge.",
    "employment_type": "FullTime",
